keyValuePair.Value: Penalty shootouts are always dramatic. How pleased were you to win?
The game against %1s was tense from start to finish. And then it was the added drama of a penalty shoot-out. What did you make of the game and how pleased are you that your team went through?
We kept our heads.

I thought the players worked hard all game and, when it mattered in the penalty shoot-out, they kept their heads and did the business. I'm delighted with their professionalism. Let's hope we can finish the job in the 90 minutes in the next round, though!

I thought the players worked hard all game and, when it mattered in the penalty shoot-out, they kept their heads and did the business. I'm delighted with their professionalism. Let's hope we can finish the job in the 90 minutes in the next round, though!
Well, we got there in the end!
To be honest, a penalty shoot-out was never part of our plans. But I'm glad we always practise spot-kicks in training. Today that preparation paid off. Well done to the boys!
To be honest, a penalty shoot-out was never part of our plans. But I'm glad we always practise spot-kicks in training. Today that preparation paid off. Well done to the boys!
We stayed focused the whole game.

That was a very tense game for the players as well as for the fans. One mistake and we'd have been out. But our lads stayed focused and kept their discipline and managed to see us through to penalties. Then it was all about composure and the keeper doing his job.
A very tense game and you came up short in the shootout. What are your thoughts?
I guess we were all expecting that a game against %1s would be close. But we maybe didn't expect a penalty shoot-out. %2s are out. What are your feelings?
It's a horrible way to go out.

I couldn't fault our lads during the game. We fought for every inch out there in normal time. But, in the shoot-out, we came up short. It's a lesson for us all. We'll never neglect practising penalties again.

I couldn't fault our lads during the game. We fought for every inch out there in normal time. But, in the shoot-out, we came up short. It's a lesson for us all. We'll never neglect practising penalties again.
We got overwhelmed by the occasion, didn't we?

Penalty shoot-outs get played out in the mind, don't they? It's about holding your nerve and not being the first to blink. We got a bit swept up in the occasion, though, and lads who are usually calm were bundles of nerves walking up to take their spot-kicks. It's a painful way to go out.

Penalty shoot-outs get played out in the mind, don't they? It's about holding your nerve and not being the first to blink. We got a bit swept up in the occasion, though, and lads who are usually calm were bundles of nerves walking up to take their spot-kicks. It's a painful way to go out.
We just have to pick ourselves up and move on.

We played well today and a penalty shoot-out is always going to be decided by luck. We can't change anything now. We have to forget it and focus on our next game. There's no point feeling sorry for ourselves.

We played well today and a penalty shoot-out is always going to be decided by luck. We can't change anything now. We have to forget it and focus on our next game. There's no point feeling sorry for ourselves.
So close to the Final. Did nerves cost your team?
You and %2s were a real match for each other during the game. But it's %1s who go out on penalties with the Final almost in sight. How disappointed are you after that?
The boys are inconsolable.

So close to the Final, the lads are gutted to miss out. It being on penalties makes it even worse. It's my job to pick them up now. I thought we played really well today and shoot-outs are just down to luck. We'll move on.
We just let nerves get to us.

There's nothing worse than going out on penalties. We did a really professional job and could maybe have won the game in normal time. But the shoot out? We just fell apart. It must have been nerves. We needed calm heads and a bit of luck. We didn't have either.

That's no way to go out, is it?

We were more than a match for %1s in normal time. And our lads pride themselves on their spot-kicks. We practise in training all the time. But today wasn't their day. I know their characters, though. They'll go away now determined never to lose in a shoot-out again.

We were more than a match for %1s in normal time. And our lads pride themselves on their spot-kicks. We practise in training all the time. But today wasn't their day. I know their characters, though. They'll go away now determined never to lose in a shoot-out again.
Congratulations! Have you got your breath back?
We knew %1s v %2s would be a tight game. It took penalties to separate you. And now you're through to the Final. What did you make of the game?
We held our nerve when it mattered.
To be honest, it could have gone either way. I'm pleased we held our nerve and went through in the shoot-out. But we can't spend time celebrating. We have to turn all our attention to the Final now.
I always trusted my lads to do it.

The boys ran themselves into the ground the whole of normal time. But they still had enough left to do what they needed to do in the shoot-out. They're a very level-headed bunch. I know I can trust them in high-pressure situations.

The boys ran themselves into the ground the whole of normal time. But they still had enough left to do what they needed to do in the shoot-out. They're a very level-headed bunch. I know I can trust them in high-pressure situations.
It's about dealing with the tension.

The game was tight. Either side could probably won it in normal time. Of course, in a shootout, you're going to need a bit of luck. But look how calm my players were. Every penalty-taker kept his head and I'm delighted we're through. I want to make sure we don't have to go to pens again in the next round, though!
Tough to lose a Final on penalties?
%1s are a good team but you matched them all the way. They won the penalty shoot-out, though, and you leave empty-handed. Could your team have done more?
I couldn't have asked for more from the boys.
I couldn't have asked for more from the boys.

It could have gone either way in the game. If anything I thought we were the better side. Which makes it all the harder to take, missing out on penalties in the end. We needed a bit of luck and we didn't get it. It's a huge disappointment. The boys deserved better than to lose a Final like that.
We should have wrapped it up in normal time.

It leaves a sour taste because I think we should have won it without the game going to penalties. It was a Final: a once-in-a-lifetime chance for some of them. Why weren't we braver, more aggressive? We should have been able to find a winning goal and not had to suffer the heartache of losing on pens.

We should have been able to find a winning goal and not had to suffer the heartache of losing on pens.
We'll take the positives from this.

I'm proud of the boys. We made it all the way through to the Final. We were up against a very good side and we took them to a shoot-out. We can improve. This %1s team will reach finals again, I'm sure of it, and we just have to make sure now that we learn from this defeat.
Incredible drama. Did your team deserve to win?
What a dramatic game. Tight, tense. We were all on the edge of our seats, right through to the shoot-out. How does it feel to have won?
Well, we gave ourselves the chance by getting to the shootout.
Well, we gave ourselves the chance by getting to the shootout.

It's taken a while for this team to come together. I'm proud of them all. The game was a real battle. But I always had the feeling our boys were going to deliver, especially in the shoot-out. They're top players. They deserve this.

The boys did a great job today.

It's all about preparation and attention to detail. We worked hard in training building up to the Final and the boys put all our plans into action. I think we proved we were ready for anything, even the penalty shoot-out.

It's all about preparation and attention to detail. We worked hard in training building up to the Final and the boys put all our plans into action. I think we proved we were ready for anything, even the penalty shoot-out.
We fought really hard for that!

The lads were fantastic today. We maybe deserved to win the game in normal time. I've got to admit I wouldn't have fancied going up to take one of those pens. The pressure must have been unbelievable. But the players kept calm and did what they had to do. They're proper %1s boys, aren't they?
